┌─ ✉️ 2FA Email Configuration & Admin Contact ────────────────────────────────────────┐
│                                                                                    │
│ 📧 **Step 1: Configure Email for Sending 2FA Codes**                               │
│ ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────   │
│ - `EMAIL_USER` is the email used to send 2FA codes whenever 2FA is triggered.      │
│   - **Recommendation:** Use the email of the company owner or the "super_admin"    │
│     (the primary administrator who passes all security checks and manages the      │
│     system). For testing, you may use your own email.                              │
│                                                                                    │
│   EMAIL_USER=yourgmail@gmail.com                                                   │
│                                                                                    │
│ - `EMAIL_PASSWORD` is a Gmail App Password (required for sending emails via Gmail).│
│                                                                                    │
│   EMAIL_PASSWORD=your_app_password                                                 │
│                                                                                    │
│   **How to Get Your Gmail App Password:**                                          │
│   1. Visit: [Google Account Security](https://myaccount.google.com/security)       │
│   2. Enable "2-Step Verification" (if not already enabled).                        │
│   3. Go to: [App Passwords](https://myaccount.google.com/apppasswords)             │
│   4. Generate a new App Password (e.g., name it "Flask Mail").                     │
│   5. Copy the 16-character password (no spaces, e.g., abcd efgh ijkl mnop).        │
│   6. Paste it as your `EMAIL_PASSWORD` (should look like: "abcdefghijklmnop").     │
│                                                                                    │
│ 📥 **Step 2: Set Admin Contact Email for Password Help**                           │
│ ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────   │
│ - `ADMIN_CONTACT_EMAIL` is used to receive requests for password changes or        │
│   account help from employees. Use an email for a trusted admin or staff member    │
│   who can edit employee accounts. For testing, use your own email.                 │
│                                                                                    │
│   ADMIN_CONTACT_EMAIL=yourgmail@gmail.com                                          │
│                                                                                    │
│ 🔒 **Tips:**                                                                       │
│ • Never share your email credentials publicly.                                     │
│ • Always use app passwords, not your real Gmail password.                          │
│ • Keep this configuration secure in your `.env` or config file.                    │
└────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘